The paper deals with language modeling, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also proposes a new type of recurrent neural network (RNN) architecture, which is a popular topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The model is designed to predict trees, which is a common task in natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also mentions the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for feature extraction, which is a popular topic in computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper uses recurrent neural networks with shared hidden layers, which is a common technique in neural engineering (cs.NE).
